    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="739" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21,
                                    1896</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 812.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 761, of the 6th
                            instant, inclosing the minister of foreign affairs denial of complicity
                            of Ottoman troops in the outrages at Marash.</p>
                <p>In this denial Tewfik Pasha states that the missionaries themselves sent
                            an address of thanks to the military commandant for the aid and
                            protection afforded them by the Imperial troops. The Department observes
                            that a similar statement is made in the letter of the vali of Aleppo
                            inclosed with your No. 756, of the 4th instant.</p>
                <p>Your letter to Mr. Lee, inquiring as to the circumstances under which the
                            missionaries sent their “address of thanks” and requesting a copy of it,
                            is approved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
